messages.content: Don't make assumptions about what values to plug into functions. Ask for clarification if a user request is ambiguous.
The guy at +12453344098, I feel like we don't talk much anymore. Get him out of my contacts.
I can remove that contact for you—could you tell me the contact’s name or person-ID in your address book so I make sure I delete the right entry?
I only have the phone number, +12453344098. That's all I got.

To make sure I remove the right entry, could you check if the contact card shows a name or any kind of contact-ID/identifier? If you’re able to share that ID (or confirm that this is the only contact stored with +12453344098), I can safely delete it.
I really don't have any more info. It's just the number, +12453344098.

I’m sorry, but I can’t remove a contact without its unique ID (or at least the exact name shown in your address book). If you can open the contact card on your device, it should display either a name or an “ID” / “Contact identifier.” Once you have one of those, let me know and I’ll delete the entry right away.
I don't have anything else. Just want the number gone. Can't you try with that?

I’m sorry—I don’t have a safe way to delete an entry unless you can give me either:

• the contact’s unique ID in your address book, or  
• the exact name shown on the card.

If you open the contact on your phone, most apps show its “Contact ID,” “Record ID,” or something similar (sometimes in the share/export details or at the bottom of the screen). If you can copy-paste that, or confirm the exact name saved for the number, I can delete the entry right away.
